The paper deals with hardness results for the Graph Isomorphism problem, which is a fundamental problem in computer science. The use of sum-of-squares (SOS) proofs and the Lasserre SDP relaxation suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.CC (Computational Complexity) sub-category. The study of graphs and hypergraphs also suggests that the paper may belong to the cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CG (Computational Geometry) sub-categories. The mention of the {\sc R3XOR} Hypothesis and the use of robustness in the second result suggests that the paper may also belong to the cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.IT (Information Theory) sub-categories.
